In VS Code, Install Remote - SSH, Remove Explorer, Live Preview and Python Extensions from microsoft.
To communicate with Browser redirect URLs, Open VS Code Settings, Uncheck Remote.SSH: Use Exec Server
Add New SSH Host...  
Login to remote Ubuntu host.

Install OpenCode to interact with schwab-mcp server:
$ curl -fsSL https://opencode.ai/install | bash
Append PATH in .profile
PATH="$HOME/.opencode/bin:$PATH"

$ python3 -m venv schwab-mcp
$ source schwab-mcp/bin/activate
(schwab-mcp) $ python -m pip install -U pip
(schwab-mcp) $ python -m pip install uv

Get Client ID and Client Secret from https://developer.schwab.com/
Create APP and Select an API Product
  Accounts and Trading Production
  Market Data Production
Order Limit
  120
Enter Callback URL(s)
  https://127.0.0.1:8182/
Wait for status to show - Ready for Use

Install schwab-mcp:
(schwab-mcp) $ uv pip install git+https://github.com/jkoelker/schwab-mcp.git
(schwab-mcp) $ uv pip install matplotlib plotly

Authenticate with Schwab to generate a token file.
(schwab-mcp) $ cd schwab-mcp
(schwab-mcp) $ uv run schwab-mcp auth --client-id YOUR_KEY --client-secret YOUR_SECRET --callback-url https://127.0.0.1:8182/
This will open a browser to log in to Schwab. Once complete, a token will be saved to ~/.local/share/schwab-mcp/token.yaml.
Add MCP Server to OpenCode:
(schwab-mcp) $ opencode mcp add

┌  Add MCP server
│
◇  Enter MCP server name
│  schwab-mcp
│
◇  Select MCP server type
│  Local
│
◆  Enter command to run
│  schwab-mcp server --client-id YOUR_KEY --client-secret YOUR_SECRET
└
Run OpenCode:
(schwab-mcp) $ opencode
Enter /models
Select DeepSeek V4 Flash Free
Ask OpenCode to:
Show me the options chain for TSLA with Greeks

NVIDIA NIM:
Get API Key at https://build.nvidia.com/explore/discover
Run the /connect command, select nvidia and paste your API Key

Install PyTorch:
(schwab-mcp) $ uv pip install torch torchvision torchaudio --index-url https://download.pytorch.org/whl/cu132
